image:image.image:title: Surfer Who Saved World From WannaCry Attack Prepares For Next Wave
image:image.image:caption: Marcus Hutchins, digital security researcher for Kryptos Logic, poses for a photograph in front of his computer in his bedroom in Ilfracombe, U.K., on Tuesday, July 4, 2017. Hutchins, the 23-year-old who saved the world from a devastating cyberattack in May was asleep in his bed in the English seaside town of Ilfracombe last week after a night of partying when another online extortion campaign spread across the globe. Photographer: Chris Ratcliffe/Bloomberg via Getty Images
